## Into

So there I was trying to install n

nobody wants to blindly install thing on their system

it may be a reasonable idea to take a look at what's being installed first



## .deb package Structure

.deb packates are `ar` archives which contain 3 parts

- `debian-binary`: a text file containing version of .deb package format
- `control.tar.xz`: checksums and package metadata
- `data.tar.xz`: actual things which will be installed on the system


